treat Claudia before Bell turfs her.

256
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:22,390
Huh.

257
00:12:22,458 --> 00:12:24,925
Excuse me, Doctor. I'm
looking for Claudia Webb.

258
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:28,279
- She's in recovery right
now and can't be seen. Yo!

259
00:12:28,331 --> 00:12:29,441
Felix.

260
00:12:29,465 --> 00:12:31,366
Go back to the waiting area.

261
00:12:31,451 --> 00:12:34,268
- Hell no. He's cool.
- Wait, who's cool?

262
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:36,971
This cat right here.

263
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:40,325
- Thanks for coming.
- How are you?

264
00:12:40,377 --> 00:12:42,710
Man, I'm freaking out,
man. I still haven't seen her.

265
00:12:42,796 --> 00:12:45,279
Do Claudia proud,
keep it together.

266
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:46,881
For her, okay?

267
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:49,400
I used to arrest this
guy every six months

268
00:12:49,469 --> 00:12:50,802
until Claudia took him in.

269
00:12:51,821 --> 00:12:53,654
Felix is one of many ex-cons

270
00:12:53,723 --> 00:12:55,334
she's hired at her
catering company.

271
00:12:55,358 --> 00:12:58,992
Claudia's an important
part of the Atlanta PD family.

272
00:12:59,062 --> 00:13:01,862
- Take special care of her.
- Don't worry.

273
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:03,231
I got your word on that, homie?

274
00:13:03,316 --> 00:13:05,749
Yeah, you got my word.

275
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:11,589
Appreciate it.

276
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:14,408
Come on.

277
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:16,928
Thank you for coming.

278
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:23,117
You have a fifth metatarsal
fracture in your foot.

279
00:13:23,185 --> 00:13:25,587
But the good news
is it's-it's nonsurgical.

280
00:13:25,655 --> 00:13:27,355
Oh!

281
00:13:27,424 --> 00:13:29,857
Yeah, but that
echocardiogram is not so good.

282
00:13:29,926 --> 00:13:31,692
Let's keep this train moving.

283
00:13:31,761 --> 00:13:34,428
Ms. Evans, your aortic valve

284
00:13:34,514 --> 00:13:36,014
has calcified and thickened,

285
00:13:36,082 --> 00:13:38,383
resulting in critical
aortic stenosis.

286
00:13:38,451 --> 00:13:40,584
It's in urgent need
of replacement.

287
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:42,086
How urgent?

288
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:43,666
D-Does it require
general anesthesia?

289
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,122
It does.

290
00:13:45,192 --> 00:13:46,969
A close friend of
mine went under

291
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,927
and when he woke,
he was a different man.

292
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:52,563
He couldn't even
recognize his own family.

293
00:13:52,632 --> 00:13:54,164
Yeah, she's right.

294
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:56,784
General anesthesia can trigger
dementia in the<i> Cocoon</i> crowd.

295
00:13:58,205 --> 00:14:01,573
Now, there is another option.

296
00:14:01,641 --> 00:14:03,357
It's, uh, nonsurgical.

297
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:05,826
- You interested?
- Yes.
- Yes.

298
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:09,948
Don't have the surgery and die.

299
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:14,051
Hey. You... watch it, buddy.

300
00:14:14,104 --> 00:14:17,572
Dr. Austin is just being
honest, but I would rather die

301
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:20,141
than go through life being
demented and confused.

302
00:14:20,227 --> 00:14:23,261
- Mom!
- I still got to go
to my belly dancing classes.

303
00:14:23,313 --> 00:14:25,124
I like this lady. Pravesh.

304
00:14:25,148 --> 00:14:28,298
- Hallway, sidebar, now.
- York.

305
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,401
Emergency, sorry, bye.

306
00:14:33,607 --> 00:14:35,106
It's Claudia.

307
00:14:35,158 --> 00:14:37,608
She started seizing and
her sats are dropping.

308
00:14:37,661 --> 00:14:39,060
Let's get her to the ICU.

309
00:14:39,129 --> 00:14:40,327
Push two of lorazepam

310
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:43,948
and prep a gram of
phenytoin on standby.

311
00:14:44,017 --> 00:14:45,216
Okay, ready?

312
00:14:45,285 --> 00:14:46,734
Let's go. One...

313
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:49,136
two... three.

314
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:04,352
- Not now.
- Easy. I come in peace.

315
00:15:04,437 --> 00:15:06,382
I-I heard about
your sister. I'm sorry.

316
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,956
- I trust she's doing better?
- Yeah.

317
00:15:09,024 --> 00:15:11,792
I have a troubled loved
one in my family as well.

318
00:15:11,861 --> 00:15:13,589
Believe me, I understand
what you're going through.

319
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,045
He's doing great now.

320
00:15:15,115 --> 00:15:17,260
He was part of the
program over at Crossroads.

321
00:15:17,284 --> 00:15:20,918
Hasn't had a relapse
since. Four years clean.

322
00:15:20,987 --> 00:15:22,253
If you'd like,

323
00:15:22,322 --> 00:15:24,922
I can help get Jessie into
the program free of charge.

324
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:26,640
Are you crazy?

325
00:15:26,709 --> 00:15:29,010
You are the last person I
want help from right now.

326
00:15:29,078 --> 00:15:31,198
Why don't you let me
take care of my family.

327
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:37,868
Hmm.

328
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:42,473
What's wrong with me?

329
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:44,436
The seizures have
been continuing

330
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:46,038
and we're trying
to figure out why.

331
00:15:46,062 --> 00:15:49,463
I have so many people,
they're like family to me.

332
00:15:49,532 --> 00:15:54,134
- They depend on me.
- I know. I've met some of them.

333
00:15:54,204 --> 00:15:56,937
I don't know what
happens to everyone

334
00:15:57,006 --> 00:15:58,956
if I'm not okay, you know?

335
00:15:59,025 --> 00:16:02,910
Look who it is.

336
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:06,680
You look great.

337
00:16:08,418 --> 00:16:11,402
You're gonna be okay.

338
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:14,421
I know.

339
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:16,607
Whatever happens...

340
00:16:16,676 --> 00:16:18,609
look how far you've come.

341
00:16:18,678 --> 00:16:21,846
I am so proud of you.

342
00:16:21,898 --> 00:16:25,116
Don't talk like that.

343
00:16:25,185 --> 00:16:26,450
Everything's gonna be fine.

344
00:16:26,519 --> 00:16:29,453
I love you. We all love you.

345
00:16:29,522 --> 00:16:30,904
I know you do.

346
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:42,433
Dr. Austin, where are you going?

347
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:45,319
To see a movie.<i> I Feel Pretty.</i>

348
00:16:45,387 --> 00:16:48,739
Centers on an ordinary woman
who struggles with feelings

349
00:16:48,792 --> 00:16:51,859
of inadequacy and
insecurity on a daily basis.

350
00:16:51,928 --> 00:16:55,113
Amy Schumer. She makes me laugh.

351
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:56,447
What do you want?

352
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:58,277
I wasn't comfortable
mentioning this earlier,

353
00:16:58,301 --> 00:17:00,935
but I can do a transcatheter
aortic valve replacement.

354
00:17:01,004 --> 00:17:02,865
So Yvonne can have
moderate sedation.

355
00:17:02,889 --> 00:17:07,141
- I need an attending.
- I'm not really a fan
of awake surgeries.

356
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:09,793
A risk we have to
take. You in or out?

357
00:17:09,863 --> 00:17:11,979
Great.

358
00:17:12,065 --> 00:17:14,498
I already bought my damn ticket!

359
00:17:14,567 --> 00:17:16,700
Are those Claudia's CSF results?

360
00:17:16,769 --> 00:17:19,136
Negative for
bacterial meningitis.

361
00:17:19,205 --> 00:17:21,050
So we're still nowhere
closer to figuring out

362
00:17:21,074 --> 00:17:23,473
- what's wrong with her.
- We're looking for a zebra.

363
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:26,343
- But we've run every test.
- Yeah, now you know the drill.

364
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:27,594
You talk.

365
00:17:27,664 --> 00:17:30,698
- To whom?
- Felix, Mambo, and Raq.

366
00:17:30,766 --> 00:17:34,502
Figure out everything
about Claudia.

367
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:36,904
Habits, hobbies, favorite food.

368
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:38,892
Hope we get closer
to a diagnosis.

369
00:17:43,646 --> 00:17:46,664
Awake? What do you mean awake?

370
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,482
Awake, meaning not sleep...

371
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:50,117
Don't you do that.

372
00:17:50,185 --> 00:17:52,453
It just... scares me.

373
00:17:52,522 --> 00:17:54,738
- When I had surgery...
- Surgery?

374
00:17:54,807 --> 00:17:56,490
For what, Yorkie?

375
00:17:56,559 --> 00:17:59,877
Mom, it wasn't a big deal.

376
00:17:59,946 --> 00:18:03,130
- Is it safe?
- Yes. And just regional anesthesia.

377
00:18:03,199 --> 00:18:05,132
- I'm in.
- Mama.

378
00:18:05,201 --> 00:18:07,485
I'm in.

379
00:18:07,537 --> 00:18:09,417
But you listen to
me, mister man.

380
00:18:09,472 --> 00:18:12,139
I'm sure you are
God's gift to medicine,

381
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:13,936
but you mind your
Ps and Qs in the OR.

382
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:15,804
If I hear anything
to the contrary,

383
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:19,730
I will wield my pen like a
mighty sword. Ask Pravesh.

384
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:23,734
I was thinking about something
else when you were talking.

385
00:18:23,803 --> 00:18:26,670
But don't bother repeating
it. I really don't care.

386
00:18:26,723 --> 00:18:29,890
I am going to save
your mother's life.

387
00:18:29,959 --> 00:18:31,225
You're welcome.

388
00:18:31,293 --> 00:18:33,122
So you've got the valve issue,

389
00:18:33,146 --> 00:18:35,579
asthma, varicose veins,

390
00:18:35,648 --> 00:18:37,214
a recent cataract surgery.

391
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,228
Any other medical history
we should know about?

392
00:18:39,252 --> 00:18:40,101
- Nope, that is everything.
- Uh...

393
00:18:40,169 --> 00:18:42,236
Yorkie, honey, give us a minute.

394
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:44,266
- But we don't have secrets,
Mother.
- No, no, honey.

395
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:46,306
I... Just one moment, sweetie.

396
00:18:46,376 --> 00:18:48,075
Okay?

397
00:18:49,996 --> 00:18:51,595
Close the door.

398
00:18:51,664 --> 00:18:54,365
I have, um...

399
00:18:54,417 --> 00:18:57,235
the little "C."

400
00:18:57,303 --> 00:19:00,571
The little "C"?
You mean big "C."

401
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:03,374
- Cancer.
- No. Chlamydia.

402
00:19:03,426 --> 00:19:06,560
We call it the little "C" in
my retirement community.

403
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:08,406
Yeah, you do.

404
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:11,448
She likes European movies.

405
00:19:11,518 --> 00:19:13,379
- At least I can tell you
that much.
- European movies...

406
00:19:13,403 --> 00:19:15,197
Mambo, not European movies,
she hates European movies.

407
00:19:15,221 --> 00:19:16,532
- She loves the outdoors.
- She does.

408
00:19:16,556 --> 00:19:18,467
- She does like the outdoors.
- She loves music.

409
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:19,373
It doesn't matter
what kind of music.

410
00:19:19,442 --> 00:19:20,725
As long as she can groove to it,

411
00:19:20,777 --> 00:19:22,054
- she digs it.
- Loves food.

412
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:23,677
Oh, she loves to cook...

413
00:19:23,746 --> 00:19:25,341
- The Hot Pocket things, the...
- The little Hot Pocket things.

414
00:19:25,365 --> 00:19:26,859
- She cooks a good meatloaf.
- She likes hiking, biking.

415
00:19:26,883 --> 00:19:28,009
She's at the water
park, she's always in...

416
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,478
she was in the
water the whole day...

417
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:31,780
- Yeah.
- It was nice. I mean, we do it every year.

418
00:19:31,804 --> 00:19:32,820
Wait.

419
00:19:32,888 --> 00:19:34,905
Wait, back up. What
did you just say?

420
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:36,635
Uh, we did an event
for the Boys & Girls Club.

421
00:19:36,659 --> 00:19:38,270
- I know, but, uh...
- We-we always do
an event for them.

422
00:19:38,294 --> 00:19:39,927
Wh-Where was it, again?

423
00:19:40,013 --> 00:19:41,023
- It was, uh, Running Rapids.
- Running Rapids.

424
00:19:41,047 --> 00:19:42,441
- Yeah, yeah, Running Rapids.
- Right?

425
00:19:42,465 --> 00:19:45,210
- Yeah.
- Yo, why are you asking
all these questions?

426
00:19:45,234 --> 00:19:46,450
Did Claudia get in the water?

427
00:19:46,519 --> 00:19:47,762
- Yeah, man, lazy river.
- Obviously.

428
00:19:47,786 --> 00:19:50,688
- Slides.
- You know what,
uh, I'll be right back.

429
00:19:51,808 --> 00:19:54,792
Hey! Yo! I got it!

430
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:56,760
Conrad, I got it.

431
00:19:56,813 --> 00:19:58,979
Get this.

432
00:19:59,048 --> 00:20:02,116
Claudia was at Running Rapids.

433
00:20:02,185 --> 00:20:05,152
- Warm, stagnant water.
- So what are we thinking?

434
00:20:05,238 --> 00:20:06,637
<i>Naegleria fowleri.</i>

435
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:08,233
98% fatal. I don't
like those odds.

436
00:20:08,257 --> 00:20:10,807
Yeah, but the signs
and the symptoms,

437
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,143
they-they-they all line up.

438
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,429
The CSF didn't show an amoeba.

439
00:20:15,498 --> 00:20:18,265
Because it was Gram
stained. I took a seminar

440
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:20,351
on brain-eating
amoebas in med school.

441
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,364
If they don't use
the Wright-Giemsa,

442
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:23,699
it's almost
impossible to detect it.

443
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:26,190
Tell the lab to rerun
the held sample

444
00:20:26,259 --> 00:20:28,508
with the Wright-Giemsa. Now.

445
00:20:35,084 --> 00:20:36,350
You need anything?

446
00:20:36,436 --> 00:20:39,353
Yes, go to work. I know
you got a million things to do.

447
00:20:39,439 --> 00:20:41,588
We're good.

448
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,876
Nice to see you two
are happening again.

449
00:20:45,945 --> 00:20:47,511
Nothing's happening again.

450
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:49,713
Well, it should be.

451
00:20:49,782 --> 00:20:52,233
- Nice to have you back, Jess.
- Conrad.

452
00:20:52,301 --> 00:20:54,685
When's the last time
you had a simple carb?

453
00:20:56,623 --> 00:20:57,738
It's been a minute.

454
00:21:03,713 --> 00:21:07,480
Eight months clean.

455
00:21:07,549 --> 00:21:10,350
Happiest I've been in forever.

456
00:21:10,419 --> 00:21:12,379
Just like that, I
threw it all away.

457
00:21:14,189 --> 00:21:17,541
Saddest part is, I
can't even tell you why.

458
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,476
It happened. It's done.

459
00:21:19,545 --> 00:21:21,826
Now I just need to get you
into a treatment program.

460
00:21:21,864 --> 00:21:23,364
Too expensive.

461
00:21:23,432 --> 00:21:25,410
I'll do outpatient again.
I'll go to meetings.

462
00:21:25,434 --> 00:21:28,552
No, Jess, we got to get
you better for good this time.

463
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:30,271
Whatever it takes.

464
00:21:30,339 --> 00:21:33,273
I'm such a liability.

465
00:21:35,811 --> 00:21:37,944
Thank you. Let me talk to her.

466
00:21:39,666 --> 00:21:41,698
You've saved me
so many times, Nicky.

467
00:21:41,751 --> 00:21:44,084
I can't keep doing this.

468
00:21:44,153 --> 00:21:46,587
- You don't deserve this.
- I'm not going anywhere.

469
00:21:46,673 --> 00:21:50,607
And don't you dare call
yourself a liability again.

470
00:21:50,677 --> 00:21:52,609
We all have our demons.

471
00:21:54,147 --> 00:21:56,881
You never judged me for mine.

472
00:21:56,933 --> 00:21:58,832
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

473
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:03,437
I really do think you might need
to make Conrad some pasta.

474
00:22:03,506 --> 00:22:05,539
He won't eat it.

475
00:22:05,608 --> 00:22:07,425
<i>Dr. Okafor.</i>

476
00:22:07,493 --> 00:22:09,638
- What are you doing here?
- Well, one of your patients

477
00:22:09,662 --> 00:22:12,412
made it into my space, so
now I'm coming into yours.

478
00:22:12,498 --> 00:22:15,199
- York.
- He's very insistent.

479
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:17,884
He also writes medical reviews

480
00:22:17,954 --> 00:22:19,920
on every major
website known to man.

481
00:22:19,989 --> 00:22:22,923
An awake surgery on his
mother with the Raptor?

482
00:22:23,009 --> 00:22:24,642
Whose grand idea was that?

483
00:22:24,711 --> 00:22:27,461
Well, now you'll have to
control his uncontrollable mouth.

484
00:22:27,547 --> 00:22:29,279
Isn't that your expertise?

485
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:31,147
It's way below my pay grade.

486
00:22:31,217 --> 00:22:32,360
You put this plan into motion.

487
00:22:32,384 --> 00:22:33,967
This surgery falls on your head.

488
00:22:36,022 --> 00:22:38,422
I'm sorry. I don't get it.
What are we doing here?

489
00:22:38,474 --> 00:22:42,759
I'm the patient, wide
awake on the table.

490
00:22:42,828 --> 00:22:44,806
I'm trying to prevent
you from giving Yvonne

491
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:47,131
a heart attack during
surgery. This isn't about me.

492
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:48,544
Well, this certainly
isn't about me.

493
00:22:48,568 --> 00:22:50,345
Is that what you thought
was-was happening here?

494
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:51,669
You were gonna train me?

495
00:22:51,737 --> 00:22:54,104
You're gonna groom
me, huh? Come on, girl.

496
00:22:54,157 --> 00:22:55,734
I don't want this
old lady to die

497
00:22:55,758 --> 00:22:57,824
because you can't
keep your mouth shut.

498
00:22:57,893 --> 00:23:00,427
Maybe this will help you
understand me better.

499
00:23:00,495 --> 00:23:02,595
My daddy looks like Chow Yun-Fat

500
00:23:02,664 --> 00:23:05,116
and my mother is the
spitting image of Mary J. Blige.

501
00:23:05,168 --> 00:23:06,612
Now, you're probably
thinking at least one of them

502
00:23:06,636 --> 00:23:08,647
served in the armed
forces, right? Wrong.

503
00:23:08,671 --> 00:23:10,337
They met at Vassar.

504
00:23:10,406 --> 00:23:13,274
A decade later they
