the same year, then, maybe,

755
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,126
I'll consider your diagnosis.

756
00:34:07,195 --> 00:34:09,115
But until then, if
you're in my OR,

757
00:34:09,164 --> 00:34:12,332
you either exit or evolve.

758
00:34:12,401 --> 00:34:14,233
That's funny.

759
00:34:14,303 --> 00:34:16,786
I didn't peg you for a doctor
who cared about accolades.

760
00:34:16,839 --> 00:34:18,238
Well, I do.

761
00:34:18,307 --> 00:34:20,106
I am who I am.

762
00:34:20,175 --> 00:34:23,409
That will never change.

763
00:34:48,069 --> 00:34:50,604
What's up, man?

764
00:34:50,672 --> 00:34:52,522
Can I help you with something?

765
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:55,559
Yeah. My little sister Nic

766
00:34:55,627 --> 00:34:59,496
wanted me to return the favor.

767
00:35:04,836 --> 00:35:06,680
Thanks for coming
all this way, Kevin.

768
00:35:06,704 --> 00:35:08,004
Ah, it wasn't so bad.

769
00:35:08,056 --> 00:35:09,701
I once drove to Kentucky
to deliver a dose.

770
00:35:09,725 --> 00:35:12,008
Did that patient make it?

771
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:14,160
Ah, afraid not.

772
00:35:14,229 --> 00:35:15,349
Never would have imagined

773
00:35:15,414 --> 00:35:18,064
a pharma CEO to
hand-deliver medication.

774
00:35:18,150 --> 00:35:19,682
Yeah.

775
00:35:19,751 --> 00:35:23,019
Well, I worked in Big
Pharma for 20 years.

776
00:35:23,071 --> 00:35:24,537
Couldn't take it anymore.

777
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:27,190
Believe it or not, I put
people before profit.

778
00:35:27,259 --> 00:35:29,842
Wait, so you only
supply miltefosine?

779
00:35:29,912 --> 00:35:31,344
Big Pharma refuses.

780
00:35:31,413 --> 00:35:35,064
Not enough people
contract<i> Naegleria.</i>

781
00:35:35,134 --> 00:35:36,515
No patients, no money.

782
00:35:36,585 --> 00:35:37,767
How do you profit?

783
00:35:37,836 --> 00:35:39,935
I don't. 48 grand a pop's

784
00:35:40,005 --> 00:35:42,722
what I need to keep the
lights on and the drug stocked.

785
00:35:42,808 --> 00:35:44,952
Speaking of which, my daughter
is getting married tomorrow.

786
00:35:44,976 --> 00:35:47,010
I should probably
get back on the road.

787
00:35:47,079 --> 00:35:49,262
Uh, who should I, uh... invoice?

788
00:35:49,348 --> 00:35:51,080
Yeah, uh...

789
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:54,550
Hey, pay that man his...

790
00:35:54,603 --> 00:35:57,237
- Uh...
- So you're the guy?

791
00:35:57,322 --> 00:36:00,423
Drove all the way from Florida
to deliver Claudia's medicine?

792
00:36:01,944 --> 00:36:03,976
It's all there.

793
00:36:09,084 --> 00:36:10,149
For your records.

794
00:36:10,218 --> 00:36:12,619
- No records.
- No records.

795
00:36:15,307 --> 00:36:16,773
Thank you, Kevin.

796
00:36:16,842 --> 00:36:18,452
I really hope this trip
was worth it for you.

797
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:20,321
It certainly will be
if Claudia survives.

798
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:21,594
Let me know, okay?

799
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:24,314
Will do.

800
00:36:28,236 --> 00:36:30,803
<i>You've reached Allie.
Please leave a message.</i>

801
00:36:30,872 --> 00:36:34,023
<i>Hi, Allie, it's Nic.
I'm pulling up now.</i>

802
00:37:10,378 --> 00:37:12,378
Allie?

803
00:37:24,359 --> 00:37:26,175
Allie?

804
00:37:43,378 --> 00:37:45,156
- Tell me about this man
that you're very close to.
- No.

805
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:47,880
- You met him.
- Oh, there he is.

806
00:37:47,966 --> 00:37:49,398
Bring it in for the real thing.

807
00:37:49,468 --> 00:37:51,028
Oh.

808
00:37:52,971 --> 00:37:55,338
- All right, big guy.
- Thank you.

809
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:57,790
- You're all right by me.
- Thank you, York.

810
00:37:57,859 --> 00:37:59,254
Now, let's get you
guys home, yeah?

811
00:37:59,278 --> 00:38:01,127
- Yeah.
- All right.

812
00:38:02,864 --> 00:38:05,460
- Just get my flowers,
don't forget.
- Yeah.

813
00:38:05,484 --> 00:38:08,585
It's clear you've chosen the
right profession, young man.

814
00:38:08,653 --> 00:38:09,852
Thank you.

815
00:38:17,663 --> 00:38:20,363
Yorkie, why is there a
syrup bottle up your butt?

816
00:38:20,432 --> 00:38:21,875
You pulled up

817
00:38:21,899 --> 00:38:24,434
the wrong "Y. Evans."

818
00:38:26,922 --> 00:38:28,722
I'm so sorry.

819
00:38:31,593 --> 00:38:33,693
It's okay.

820
00:38:33,761 --> 00:38:35,361
I have chlamydia.

821
00:38:37,849 --> 00:38:41,384
Those... look...

822
00:38:41,436 --> 00:38:43,836
good.

823
00:38:43,905 --> 00:38:46,538
How we feeling?

824
00:38:46,607 --> 00:38:48,975
Can you tell us your name?

825
00:39:00,172 --> 00:39:02,956
Yo, Felix.

826
00:39:03,024 --> 00:39:04,991
Hey, what's up?

827
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:06,326
What?

828
00:39:06,394 --> 00:39:08,978
Oh, what's up?

829
00:39:09,047 --> 00:39:10,246
She okay?

830
00:39:10,314 --> 00:39:13,266
She's awake?

831
00:39:13,352 --> 00:39:15,752
This one's all you.

832
00:39:17,272 --> 00:39:19,272
Yeah.

833
00:39:19,340 --> 00:39:20,740
She's awake.

834
00:39:20,809 --> 00:39:22,408
And she's okay.

835
00:39:22,477 --> 00:39:23,955
In fact, she's doing great.

836
00:39:23,979 --> 00:39:26,696
And she can't wait
to see all you guys.

837
00:39:28,416 --> 00:39:30,332
Hey, man.

838
00:39:30,402 --> 00:39:31,834
You did good, man.

839
00:39:31,903 --> 00:39:33,836
You did real good.

840
00:39:37,108 --> 00:39:38,269
Oh!

841
00:39:38,293 --> 00:39:40,143
I love you, D.

842
00:39:45,717 --> 00:39:47,399
Oh, God.

843
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:51,520
Man, not again.

844
00:39:53,524 --> 00:39:56,042
You know, only four
people in the U.S. have

845
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:58,494
ever survived<i> Naegleria fowleri.</i>

846
00:39:58,563 --> 00:40:00,262
You just saved the fifth.

847
00:40:00,315 --> 00:40:01,659
It would not have been
great if you'd frozen Claudia

848
00:40:01,683 --> 00:40:04,133
to death, but you didn't.

849
00:40:04,186 --> 00:40:05,651
No, today you gambled

850
00:40:05,737 --> 00:40:08,337
on unorthodox
medicine and you won.

851
00:40:08,407 --> 00:40:10,874
Had you not won...

852
00:40:10,942 --> 00:40:12,587
you'd be walking
out of this hospital

853
00:40:12,611 --> 00:40:14,143
for the last time,

854
00:40:14,196 --> 00:40:15,373
to join the ranks
of the unemployed

855
00:40:15,397 --> 00:40:16,477
along with Nurse Nevin.

856
00:40:17,949 --> 00:40:19,082
This is my hospital.

857
00:40:20,118 --> 00:40:22,652
It's not your casino.

858
00:40:22,704 --> 00:40:24,504
Enjoy your drinks.

859
00:40:24,573 --> 00:40:27,390
Ah.

860
00:40:27,459 --> 00:40:29,291
Wait, wait.

861
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:31,494
What just... what just happened?

862
00:40:31,546 --> 00:40:32,762
He said you're amazing.

863
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:38,100
And he can fire you
whenever he wants.

864
00:40:38,169 --> 00:40:39,736
Hello.

865
00:40:39,805 --> 00:40:41,416
<i>They set me up.</i>

866
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,538
Who set you up?

867
00:40:42,607 --> 00:40:44,424
Where are you?

868
00:40:44,492 --> 00:40:46,893
Atlanta Detention Center.

869
00:40:46,978 --> 00:40:49,195
I'm on my way.

870
00:40:49,281 --> 00:40:51,581
No, Conrad, listen to me.

871
00:40:51,650 --> 00:40:53,026
There's nothing you
can do for me right now.

872
00:40:53,050 --> 00:40:55,635
There's something
else I need help with.

873
00:40:56,904 --> 00:40:58,504
There you are.

874
00:40:58,573 --> 00:40:59,584
I was just about to call you.

875
00:40:59,608 --> 00:41:00,884
I tried Nic, like,
a hundred times.

876
00:41:00,908 --> 00:41:01,974
She's not answering.

877
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:03,776
Where you going, Jessie?

878
00:41:03,844 --> 00:41:05,556
Inman Park. Gonna
meet up with some friends,

879
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:07,446
just clear my head.

880
00:41:07,515 --> 00:41:09,515
It'll be good for me.

881
00:41:09,584 --> 00:41:11,650
Thanks for everything yesterday.

882
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:13,886
Sit down, Jessie.

883
00:41:13,955 --> 00:41:16,355
Yeah, I'm good.

884
00:41:16,424 --> 00:41:18,991
Did Nic send you?

885
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,788
Is that why she's not
answering my calls?

886
00:41:20,812 --> 00:41:23,913
You know, I don't
need this right now.

887
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:25,910
And I've been discharged.
Dr. Whatever said I could go.

888
00:41:25,934 --> 00:41:28,600
Uh, Nic got you a
place at Crossroads;

889
00:41:28,669 --> 00:41:30,085
it's a three-week program.

890
00:41:30,155 --> 00:41:31,532
- Crossroads.
- Mm-hmm.

891
00:41:31,556 --> 00:41:33,422
Nice.

892
00:41:34,626 --> 00:41:35,791
See, this is what happens.

893
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:37,943
People make
decisions about my life,

894
00:41:38,029 --> 00:41:40,429
- and that's not okay.
- We'll do this together.

895
00:41:40,499 --> 00:41:41,542
Yeah, I said I'll do
the outpatient stuff,

896
00:41:41,566 --> 00:41:42,698
I'll go to meetings...

897
00:41:42,751 --> 00:41:44,595
You tried it last time,
and it didn't work.

898
00:41:44,619 --> 00:41:46,586
I'm leaving.

899
00:41:46,654 --> 00:41:48,304
Move, Conrad.

900
00:41:48,373 --> 00:41:49,973
You almost died last night.

901
00:41:50,041 --> 00:41:52,103
Would you have come
to my funeral if I did?

902
00:41:52,127 --> 00:41:54,594
You care now?

903
00:41:54,662 --> 00:41:56,913
We're family?

904
00:41:56,965 --> 00:41:58,464
Please.

905
00:41:58,550 --> 00:42:01,700
You're still just
passing through.

906
00:42:01,770 --> 00:42:05,121
Well, I'm here right now, and
I'm not leaving without you.

907
00:42:06,824 --> 00:42:08,707
Where the hell is my sister?

908
00:42:10,679 --> 00:42:12,290
Your sister's going through
a hard time right now...

909
00:42:12,314 --> 00:42:14,074
- Is she okay?
- She will be.

910
00:42:17,068 --> 00:42:18,534
Your sister loves you very much.

911
00:42:18,603 --> 00:42:20,520
She loves more than anything.

912
00:42:20,588 --> 00:42:24,240
If you don't want to do
it for you, do it for her.

913
00:42:26,461 --> 00:42:28,421
I wasn't always the
one screwing up.

914
00:42:31,049 --> 00:42:33,783
Oh.

915
00:42:33,852 --> 00:42:36,920
I guess you don't know Nic
as well as you think you do.

916
00:42:40,741 --> 00:42:41,974
I'll be waiting outside.

917
00:42:42,043 --> 00:42:43,493
We'll leave when you're ready.

